ENTRY       EC 6.3.2.33                 Enzyme
NAME        tetrahydrosarcinapterin synthase;
            H4MPT:alpha-L-glutamate ligase;
            MJ0620;
            MptN protein
CLASS       Ligases;
            Forming carbon-nitrogen bonds;
            Acid-D-amino-acid ligases (peptide synthases)
SYSNAME     tetrahydromethanopterin:alpha-L-glutamate ligase (ADP-forming)
REACTION    ATP + tetrahydromethanopterin + L-glutamate = ADP + phosphate + 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrosarcinapterin [RN:R09594]
ALL_REAC    R09594
SUBSTRATE   ATP [CPD:C00002];
            tetrahydromethanopterin [CPD:C01217];
            L-glutamate [CPD:C00025]
PRODUCT     ADP [CPD:C00008];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009];
            5,6,7,8-tetrahydrosarcinapterin [CPD:C18802]
COMMENT     This enzyme catalyses the biosynthesis of 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrosarcinapterin, a modified form of tetrahydromethanopterin found in the Methanosarcinales. It does not require K+, and does not discriminate between ATP and GTP [1].
